```

## System initialization

The cell below establishes the distributed connection between the master and worker nodes and checks that the worker node is reachable before starting the simulation.

```elixir
Node.connect(:"worker@127.0.0.1")
:net_adm.ping(:"worker@127.0.0.1")

```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
:pong
```

The code below starts the core coordination and control processes and confirms successful initialization by reporting the number of cell and active BEAM processes.

```elixir
# Optional: two if conditions used to ensure a clean restart 
if pid = Process.whereis(Life.Coordinator), do: Process.exit(pid, :kill)
if pid = Process.whereis(Life.Controller), do: Process.exit(pid, :kill)

{:ok, _} = Life.Coordinator.start_link([])
{:ok, _} = Life.Controller.start_link([])

cell_count = Life.Coordinator.get_cells()
process_count = Process.list() |> length()

IO.puts("✓ #{cell_count} cell processes created")
IO.puts("✓ Total BEAM processes: #{process_count}")

```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
✓ 900 cell processes created
✓ Total BEAM processes: 546
```

